SIMPLE: diatomaceous_earth
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: diatomaceous earth
<hw>di`a*to*ma"ceous earth`</hw> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>, <def>a deposit of
fine, usually white, siliceous material, composed mainly of the shells
of the microscopic plants called <compof>diatoms</compof>; also called
<altname>infusorial earth</altname>, <altname>kieselguhr</altname>, and
<altname>diatomite</altname>. It is used in polishing powder, and in the
manufacture of dynamite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>diatomic</ent>⟦br⟧
